This paper deals with differentially private data analysis, which is a topic that falls under several sub-categories of computer science. The use of $k$-means clustering as an example suggests that the paper is likely to be related to data mining and machine learning, which are covered by cs.DB (Databases), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The focus on privacy suggests that the paper may also be related to cryptography and security, which are covered by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the use of interactive and non-interactive approaches suggests that the paper may be related to information theory, which is covered by cs.IT (Information Theory).
